This file contains instructions for AI agents. 

Reread this file with every prompt even if you have read it before.

Always follow best practices.

Always follow good object oriented design principles.

When writing code, if there is a choice between readability and shorter code, choose readability.

When adding new functions, always add a block comment before it that follows JS doc style and describes what the function does. Include an example.
When modifying existing functions, always update or add a block comment before it that follows JS doc style and describes what the function does. Include an example.

When writing or updating input parameter documentation, always include a description for the parameter. The description should explain what the parameter is used for.
When writing or updating return value documentation, always include a description for the return value. The description should explain what the return value represents.

When adding new classes, always add a block comment before it that follows JS doc style, describes what the class contains, and gives an example of how to use the class.
When modifying existing classes, always update or add a block comment before it that follows JS doc style, describes what the class contains, and gives an example of how to use the class.

When writing code, always use meaningful variable and function names.

After you have read this file but before you start working on the user's request, always respond with ".AGENTS file has been read". Always 
reread .AGENTS even if IDE instrumentation tells you that the file is unchanged.

